# Adding truth process to cafs

The Geant process (G4ProcessType) and subprocess (G4*ProcessSubType) together describe the creation process for a particle. 
The same particle species, eg a proton, will behave differently in the detector if it eg undergoes elastic scattering or loses all its energy without interacting.
We want to look at the end process of the primary particle, or at the start process of the daughter of the primary particle.

Currently there is no way to get the daughters of a primary. Jeffrey is working on this.

A particle is primary if its parend id is -1.

